      "date": "2012-05-14 02:14:03.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 8:\n\nOleg, this patch is correctly focussed on only removing the ext3 code. While it is also good to remove the 2.6.18 code, that should be done in a separate patch. This patch is itself a good cleanup of old ext3 code, and I think it should land as-is.\n\nIt is fine to get a follow-on patch that does more cleanup of obsolete code on the server.  This hasn't been done by EMC since they are only focussed the client code.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 8
    },
